# Skeleton Patterns

**Domain**: `'skel'` | **Prefix**: `skel_` | **Indent**: Tabs

## ACF Blocks

### Block Folder Structure

Each block is self-contained in `blocks/{slug}/`:

```
blocks/
  main-hero/
    main-hero.php      ŌåÉ Block template
    main-hero.scss     ŌåÉ Source styles
    main-hero.css      ŌåÉ Compiled styles (auto-generated, git-ignored)
    main-hero.js       ŌåÉ Block scripts
    main-hero.json     ŌåÉ ACF field group
    preview.png        ŌåÉ Block preview image
  blank/               ŌåÉ Template for new blocks
    blank.php
    blank.scss
    blank.js
    blank.json
```

### Register New Block

In `blocks/config.php`:

```php
$block_types = array( 'Hero Slider', 'New Block' );
```

### Auto-Generated Files

When registered, creates in `blocks/{slug}/`:

- `{slug}.php` - Block template
- `{slug}.scss` - Block styles (compiles to `{slug}.css`)
- `{slug}.js` - Block scripts (always generated)
- `{slug}.json` - ACF field group
- Uses `blocks/blank/` as template source

### Conditional Asset Loading

CSS/JS only enqueues when block is present on page via `has_block()`. No manual enqueuing needed.

### Block Template Structure

Source of truth: `blocks/blank/blank.php`. Use the helpers from `functions/acf-block-helpers.php` ŌĆö never inline the preview check, display gate, or `$spacing`/`$custom_*` unpacking.

```php
<?php
if ( skel_render_block_preview( $block ) ) {
	return;
}

if ( ! skel_should_display_block() ) {
	return;
}

$items       = get_field( 'items' );
$dev_options = skel_get_block_developer_options();
?>

<section
	class="{slug}-section section <?php echo esc_attr( "{$dev_options['display_class']} {$dev_options['spacing_top']} {$dev_options['spacing_bottom']} {$dev_options['custom_classes']}" ); ?>"
	style="<?php echo esc_attr( "{$dev_options['spacing_top_custom']} {$dev_options['spacing_bottom_custom']} {$dev_options['custom_css']}" ); ?>"
	id="<?php echo esc_attr( $dev_options['unique_id'] ); ?>">
	<div class="container">
		<?php if ( is_array( $items ) && ! empty( $items ) ) : ?>
			<?php foreach ( $items as $item ) : ?><!-- Content --><?php endforeach; ?>
		<?php endif; ?>
	</div>
</section>
```

## HTML Structure

| Element         | Class Pattern     | Example                           |
| --------------- | ----------------- | --------------------------------- |
| Section wrapper | `*-section`       | `hero-section`, `faq-section`     |
| Content block   | `*-block`         | `content-block`, `img-block`      |
| Image container | `img-cover-block` | With `img-cover` class on `<img>` |
| Grid container  | `*-grid`          | `items-grid`, `cards-grid`        |
| Row container   | `row`             | Flex row with columns             |

## Data Attributes

### Animations

| Attribute               | Purpose                          |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `data-inview`           | Viewport trigger for animations  |
| `data-aos="fade-up"`    | AOS animation type               |
| `data-aos-stagger-item` | Child elements stagger animation |

### Toggles

| Attribute                   | Purpose                          |
| --------------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| `data-toggle-click="name"`  | Click trigger                    |
| `data-toggle-hover="name"`  | Hover trigger                    |
| `data-toggle-link="name"`   | Target element                   |
| `data-toggle-group="group"` | Group (only one active)          |
| `data-toggle-lenis`         | Disable Lenis scroll when active |

### Other

| Attribute              | Purpose                |
| ---------------------- | ---------------------- |
| `data-sticky`          | Sticky element         |
| `data-close-scroll`    | Close on scroll        |
| `data-close-click-out` | Close on outside click |
| `data-esc`             | Close on Escape key    |
| `data-dialog="id"`     | Dialog trigger/target  |

## Helper Functions

```php
// Icons
<?php echo skel_get_svg( 'arrow-right', [ 'class' => 'icon', 'aria-hidden' => 'true' ] ); ?>

// URLs
<a href="<?php echo skel_get_phone_url( '+971 50 123 4567' ); ?>">Call</a>

// Text
<?php echo esc_html( skel_get_the_excerpt( 20 ) ); ?>
<?php echo esc_html( skel_get_text_shorter( $text, 100 ) ); ?>

// Direction (WPML)
<div class="<?php echo esc_attr( skel_direction_class() ); ?>">
<div class="<?php echo esc_attr( skel_swiper_direction_class() ); ?>">

// oEmbed
$src = skel_extract_oembed_src( get_field( 'video' ) );

// Random ID
$dialog_id = skel_get_random_string();
```

## Image Pattern

**Always use `wp_get_attachment_image()` instead of manual image output:**

```php
<?php
$image_id = $item['image'];
if ( $image_id ) :
	echo wp_get_attachment_image(
		$image_id,
		'w768',
		false,
		[
			'class'   => 'img-cover',
			'loading' => 'lazy',
			'sizes'   => '(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px',
		]
	);
endif;
?>
```

`.img-cover-block` + `.img-cover` are styled globally in `src/sass/partials/utilities/_images.scss` ŌĆö block SCSS keeps only the diff. See `pitfalls.mdc` #2.

## JavaScript Pattern

```javascript
(() => {
	const elements = document.querySelectorAll('.js-component');
	if (!elements.length) return;

	elements.forEach((el, i) => {
		el.classList.add(`component-${i}`);
		// Logic
	});
})();
```

## Swiper Pattern

```php
<div class="swiper <?php echo esc_attr( skel_swiper_direction_class() ); ?> block-slider">
	<div class="swiper-wrapper">
		<?php foreach ( $items as $item ) : ?>
			<div class="swiper-slide"><!-- Slide --></div>
		<?php endforeach; ?>
	</div>
	<div class="swiper-pagination"></div>
	<?php if ( count( $items ) > 1 ) :
		get_template_part( 'template-parts/swiper-navigation', null, [ 'style' => 'floating' ] );
	endif; ?>
</div>
```

## CSS Classes

### State Classes (JS)

- `js-active` - Active/open state
- `js-visible` - Visible in viewport
- `js-open` - Open state (menus, modals)

### Spacing Classes

- `st-sm`, `st-md`, `st-lg`, `st-xl` - Spacing top
- `sb-sm`, `sb-md`, `sb-lg`, `sb-xl` - Spacing bottom

### Background Classes

- `bg-white`, `bg-light`, `bg-dark`

